                            </ol>
                            <h2>Starting Position</h2>
                            <p>Both competitors must start by doing the Sumo stomp and walking up to each other. They must face each other, and place both arms on their opponents opposite shoulders.
                            Bouts can only commence when the Centre Referee calls start.
                            Bouts can only finish when the Centre Referee calls stop.
                            The Centre referee is the only one who can start or stop bouts and issue warnings.</p>
                            <h2>Legal Scoring Techniques</h2>
                            <p>You can push your opponent out of the ring; both feet of your opponent must be out to score a point.
                            You can pull your opponent down by the shoulders or arms; a point will be scored, where any part of their body touch the mat, except their feet.</p>
                            <h2>Illegal Techniques</h2>
                            <p>No throws of any type allowed.
                            No Pinching of opponentâ€™s body allowed.
